WEBVTT

00:21.590 --> 00:23.000
Dierdre: I need to speak
to the person

00:23.200 --> 00:24.480
who is assigned
to my daughter's file.

00:24.670 --> 00:27.040
She thinks she has harmed
someone with her mind.

00:27.240 --> 00:28.440
Rowan: If I knew
who my parents were,

00:28.640 --> 00:30.610
maybe I would understand
what happened.

00:30.810 --> 00:33.010
Billy: It's just hard to believe
this is my patient.

00:33.210 --> 00:34.440
They don't like it
when her shot is late.

00:34.640 --> 00:36.970
Woman: I told you not to
encourage him.

00:37.170 --> 00:39.490
Girl: Uncle Cortland.And such a delightful surprise.

00:39.690 --> 00:40.710
Lasher: That baby's coming.

00:40.910 --> 00:42.010
She will change your life
forever.

00:42.210 --> 00:43.800
[Screaming] Carlotta!

00:44.000 --> 00:46.110
Carlotta: This baby can never
ever know who she is.

00:46.310 --> 00:48.460
Who is going to
keep my daughter safe?

00:48.660 --> 00:49.930
I will keep your daughter safe.

00:52.100 --> 00:54.060
[groans, coughs]

00:57.850 --> 00:59.240
[goat bleats]

01:10.160 --> 01:12.340
- [coughing, sobbing]
- [speaking indistinctly]

01:13.860 --> 01:16.270
Shh. Hush now.

01:16.470 --> 01:19.010
<i>[light music]</i>

01:19.210 --> 01:20.880
[chickens clucking]

01:21.080 --> 01:23.100
[goat bleats]

01:23.300 --> 01:30.100
<i>♪ </i>

02:07.350 --> 02:10.140
[birds calling]

02:42.870 --> 02:45.780
<i>[ominous music]</i>

02:58.360 --> 03:01.330
<i>♪ </i>

03:01.530 --> 03:03.980
Elderberry.

03:04.180 --> 03:05.510
Pennyroyal.

03:05.710 --> 03:07.160
<i>Hawthorn.</i>

03:07.360 --> 03:09.210
Lady's Mantle.

03:09.400 --> 03:10.510
Burdock.

03:10.710 --> 03:11.690
[moans, chuckles]

03:11.890 --> 03:12.720
<i>Salvia.</i>

03:16.730 --> 03:19.550
[groaning]

03:22.380 --> 03:23.830
[groans]

03:24.030 --> 03:26.570
[crows cawing]

03:26.770 --> 03:32.920
<i>♪ </i>

03:33.120 --> 03:36.580
<i>[voices whispering "Suzanne"]</i>

03:36.780 --> 03:39.540
<i>[choir singing indistinctly]</i>

03:39.740 --> 03:44.100
<i>♪ </i>

03:48.410 --> 03:50.890
<i>[touch tones beeping]</i>

03:52.110 --> 03:54.550
<i>[line trills]</i>

03:54.750 --> 03:57.340
<i>- South Bay Adoption Agency.</i>
- Hello. Hi.

03:57.540 --> 04:00.430
I was hoping to speak
to someone about an adoption.

04:00.630 --> 04:02.130
<i>- Are you</i>
<i>a prospective parent?</i>

04:02.330 --> 04:06.520
- No, uh, it's actually--
it's about my own adoption.

04:06.720 --> 04:11.350
My adoptive mother
has just died,

04:11.550 --> 04:13.700
and I j--I guess I just thought
I should tell someone,

04:13.900 --> 04:16.320
just in case
maybe it changes something.

04:16.520 --> 04:17.880
<i>Oh, I'm sorry to hear that,</i>

04:18.080 --> 04:19.620
<i>but what were you</i>
<i>hoping to change?</i>

04:19.820 --> 04:23.580
- I don't know, I--
it's just, my--my mother

04:23.780 --> 04:27.110
had been trying to help me
find my birth parents,

04:27.310 --> 04:32.290
and she contacted you guys
several times about, uh,

04:32.490 --> 04:36.030
the release of my records
about my adoption back in 1991.

04:36.230 --> 04:38.120
<i>- 1991.</i>
- Yes.

04:38.320 --> 04:40.300
It was a closed adoption.

04:40.500 --> 04:42.470
<i>- Not at this agency,</i>
<i>it wasn't.</i>

04:42.670 --> 04:46.000
- [sighs]
What? You--w--uh--

04:46.200 --> 04:48.000
you mean I can see my records?

04:48.200 --> 04:49.570
<i>- What I mean</i>
<i>is that we weren't</i>

04:49.770 --> 04:52.090
<i>facilitating adoptions</i>
<i>in 1991.</i>

04:52.290 --> 04:55.220
<i>Our agency didn't open</i>
<i>until 1995.</i>

04:55.420 --> 04:57.400
- That's not--
[laughs]

04:57.600 --> 05:00.490
No--no, my mother and I

05:00.690 --> 05:03.010
discussed South Bay Adoption
many times.

05:03.210 --> 05:05.410
She drove me by your offices.

05:05.610 --> 05:09.270
This is--d--I mean, she told me
the story every year.

05:10.670 --> 05:13.630
<i>- I'm sorry, there must have</i>
<i>been some misunderstanding.</i>

05:13.830 --> 05:15.580
[sighs]

05:17.980 --> 05:19.120
<i>Hello?</i>

05:19.320 --> 05:24.730
[phone beeps]

05:24.930 --> 05:28.030
[boats creaking]

05:35.470 --> 05:38.820
[engine humming]

05:50.270 --> 05:53.020
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

05:53.220 --> 05:59.370
<i>♪ </i>

06:03.070 --> 06:05.690
<i>[voices whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

06:05.890 --> 06:10.210
<i>♪ </i>

06:10.410 --> 06:13.210
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

06:25.480 --> 06:28.350
<i>[chanting indistinctly]</i>

06:35.270 --> 06:36.410
<i>- Do you remember</i>
<i>I promised you once</i>

06:36.610 --> 06:38.150
<i>that your life would change,</i>

06:38.350 --> 06:41.500
that everything
would be better?

06:41.700 --> 06:43.670
- I remember.
- Ah.

06:45.240 --> 06:46.760
That change is coming,
my love.

06:48.460 --> 06:51.340
I found her, your daughter.

06:51.540 --> 06:53.390
She's alive.

06:53.590 --> 06:55.780
She's in a place
as dark as this one.

06:55.980 --> 06:58.740
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:58.940 --> 07:05.010
<i>♪ </i>

07:05.210 --> 07:08.490
I want to see her.

07:08.690 --> 07:10.920
I need to see her.

07:11.120 --> 07:13.450
- Then you need to wake up
and take control.

07:13.650 --> 07:15.570
Use the power
that's rightly yours.

07:16.970 --> 07:18.400
Do you hear me?

07:20.230 --> 07:21.450
Wake up.

07:22.450 --> 07:23.720
Wake up.

07:23.920 --> 07:24.970
Wake up.

07:29.630 --> 07:32.470
- All right.
Open up, now. Don't fuss.

07:32.670 --> 07:33.810
Open.

07:37.290 --> 07:38.250
Deirdre?

07:40.250 --> 07:41.780
Are you okay?

07:41.980 --> 07:48.780
<i>♪ </i>

07:51.130 --> 07:54.490
<i>[eerie music]</i>

07:54.690 --> 07:57.490
<i>[voices whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

07:57.690 --> 08:00.190
<i>♪ </i>

08:00.390 --> 08:04.150
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

08:04.350 --> 08:10.800
<i>♪ </i>

08:26.160 --> 08:28.990
[seagulls cawing]

08:34.040 --> 08:35.270
<i>[stovetop clicks,</i>
<i>flame whooshes]</i>

08:35.470 --> 08:36.360
<i>- In the meantime,</i>
<i>a really calm</i>

08:36.560 --> 08:37.970
<i>and cooler start to the week,</i>

08:38.170 --> 08:40.270
<i>with temperatures</i>
<i>in the lower 70s.</i>

08:40.470 --> 08:43.710
<i>[exciting music playing]</i>

08:43.910 --> 08:46.020
<i>- The charred body</i>
<i>of a 32-year-old woman</i>

08:46.220 --> 08:47.460
<i>was discovered</i>
<i>on the outskirts</i>

08:47.660 --> 08:49.110
<i>of Phoenix this morning.</i>

08:49.310 --> 08:51.680
<i>Sources say her hands</i>
<i>and feet were bound</i>

08:51.880 --> 08:54.460
<i>before she was doused</i>
<i>with gasoline and set aflame.</i>

08:54.660 --> 08:56.730
<i>If you have any information</i>
<i>regarding this case,</i>

08:56.930 --> 08:59.080
<i>please contact</i>
<i>your local police department.</i>

08:59.280 --> 09:01.850
<i>Detectives cannot offer any</i>
<i>other information at this--</i>

09:04.810 --> 09:07.610
[keyboard clacking]

09:07.810 --> 09:08.900
[computer beeps]

09:13.120 --> 09:15.480
<i>[line trills]</i>

09:15.680 --> 09:16.790
<i>Hi. It's Rowan.</i>

09:16.990 --> 09:19.140
I, uh--
I just checked the schedule

09:19.340 --> 09:20.620
for today,
and I'm not on it.

09:20.820 --> 09:23.230
Can you see
what the--the mistake is?

09:23.430 --> 09:24.830
[sighs]

09:28.140 --> 09:29.500
Oh.

09:29.700 --> 09:30.710
Okay. Yeah.

09:33.880 --> 09:35.110
Yeah, I'll talk to him.

09:35.310 --> 09:36.980
[phone beeps]

09:37.180 --> 09:40.070
[pan sizzling]

09:40.270 --> 09:41.280
Oh, sh--

09:45.070 --> 09:46.520
[birds cawing]

09:46.710 --> 09:48.690
<i>- You know,</i>
<i>after I lost my father,</i>

09:48.890 --> 09:51.000
I'm not ashamed to admit
it took me a couple of weeks

09:51.200 --> 09:53.380
to remember which end
of the scalpel was up.

09:54.780 --> 09:56.480
With all due respect,

09:56.680 --> 09:59.570
I've done six procedures
since Monday,

09:59.770 --> 10:01.270
all positive outcomes.

10:01.470 --> 10:03.750
- Yeah, I looked
at those tapes.

10:03.950 --> 10:05.580
<i>On average, your patients</i>
<i>had been under anesthesia</i>

10:05.780 --> 10:08.150
<i>1.3 times longer</i>
<i>than they were in the past.</i>

10:08.340 --> 10:09.890
<i>It's a significant increase.</i>

10:10.090 --> 10:11.760
- That's still faster
than anyone else on the team.

10:11.960 --> 10:13.670
- You're not on your game,
Rowan.

10:13.870 --> 10:15.070
Let yourself take a break.

10:15.260 --> 10:16.670
Please, Dr. Keck.

10:18.020 --> 10:21.200
Just tell me what I need to do
to get back on the rotation.

10:21.400 --> 10:23.550
- [sighs]
Two floors up.

10:23.750 --> 10:25.900
Dr. Davis on the psych team.

10:26.100 --> 10:28.110
She gives you the all-clear,
you're back in business.

10:32.290 --> 10:35.130
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

10:35.330 --> 10:42.170
<i>♪ </i>

11:04.850 --> 11:06.600
- I'm just gonna ask you
a few questions.

11:06.790 --> 11:08.470
You can answer as long
or as short as you like.

11:08.670 --> 11:10.510
Ask away.

11:10.710 --> 11:12.380
<i>How are you sleeping?</i>

11:12.580 --> 11:14.680
<i>Good. Pretty good, you know.</i>

11:16.940 --> 11:18.080
<i>And emotionally?</i>

11:18.280 --> 11:21.090
<i>Are you feeling anxious,</i>
<i>volatile?</i>

11:21.290 --> 11:22.180
<i>Any mood swings?</i>

11:22.380 --> 11:23.530
<i>- I'd--I'd have to say no.</i>

11:23.720 --> 11:27.130
[sobbing]

11:30.310 --> 11:33.060
<i>- You lost your mother</i>
<i>two weeks ago.</i>

11:33.260 --> 11:34.930
<i>Yet you haven't missed</i>
<i>a day of work.</i>

11:35.130 --> 11:38.190
- Honestly, um, I'm at my best
when I'm working.

11:38.390 --> 11:39.760
<i>And that's why I'm hoping</i>

11:39.960 --> 11:41.060
<i>you'll let me</i>
<i>get back to it soon.</i>

11:42.530 --> 11:44.330
<i>I'm hoping so too, Rowan.</i>

11:44.530 --> 11:47.370
<i>Tell me, what is it about work</i>
<i>that makes you feel better?</i>

11:48.890 --> 11:50.190
Healing people.

11:53.590 --> 11:55.370
Nothing feels better than that.

11:56.980 --> 11:58.860
<i>I agree.</i>

11:59.060 --> 12:01.480
<i>That's what I like</i>
<i>about being a doctor too.</i>

12:01.680 --> 12:03.300
<i>You've been through</i>
<i>a great deal of trauma,</i>

12:03.500 --> 12:05.740
<i>and there's nothing wrong</i>
<i>with acknowledging that.</i>

12:05.940 --> 12:07.920
I have acknowledged it.

12:08.120 --> 12:10.400
I was at my mother's grave
yesterday, and I cried.

12:10.600 --> 12:11.700
Is that what you want to hear?

12:11.900 --> 12:13.050
<i>That's one way to grieve.</i>

12:13.250 --> 12:14.740
Talking is another.

12:17.790 --> 12:18.920
Tell me about Daniel Lemle.

12:20.920 --> 12:22.190
- Who?
<i>- Daniel Lemle?</i>

12:22.390 --> 12:23.620
<i>It says you were present</i>
<i>when he died.</i>

12:25.400 --> 12:27.850
Why is that in my work file?

12:28.050 --> 12:29.770
Did Keck put that in there?

12:29.960 --> 12:31.420
Tell me what's upsetting you.

12:31.620 --> 12:32.720
What's upsetting me is,

12:32.920 --> 12:34.510
his death
had nothing to do with me.

12:34.710 --> 12:36.030
<i>But you were there.</i>

12:36.230 --> 12:37.950
You witnessed it.
That must have been hard.

12:38.150 --> 12:40.300
I see death every day.

12:40.500 --> 12:44.040
In a hospital, sure.

12:44.240 --> 12:47.650
In a controlled setting,
not unexpectedly when you--ugh!

12:47.850 --> 12:49.700
Are you okay?

12:49.900 --> 12:51.470
Oh, Jesus.

12:54.430 --> 12:57.050
I get these all the time.
Just...

12:57.250 --> 12:58.580
[sighs]
Give me a second.

12:58.780 --> 13:01.660
[pills rattling]

13:02.610 --> 13:03.660
Sorry.

13:05.180 --> 13:06.410
Right.
[clears throat]

13:06.610 --> 13:07.980
I'm just imagining that

13:08.180 --> 13:10.330
even for a seasoned surgeon
like yourself--

13:10.530 --> 13:13.500
<i>[voices whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

13:13.700 --> 13:16.290
<i>[tense music]</i>

13:16.490 --> 13:23.290
<i>♪ </i>

13:27.070 --> 13:29.900
[crows cawing]

13:33.470 --> 13:35.170
Fuck.

13:36.650 --> 13:39.300
<i>[singing indistinctly]</i>

13:40.350 --> 13:41.660
<i>[whispering] Rowan.</i>

13:41.860 --> 13:47.490
<i>♪ </i>

13:47.690 --> 13:49.670
[gasps]

13:49.870 --> 13:56.710
<i>♪ </i>

14:11.640 --> 14:12.870
<i>[camera shutter snapping]</i>

14:13.070 --> 14:15.870
[breathing shallowly]

14:16.070 --> 14:22.870
<i>♪ </i>

14:26.660 --> 14:28.060
[engine turning over]

14:28.260 --> 14:34.880
<i>♪ </i>

15:02.260 --> 15:04.910
[panting]

15:16.100 --> 15:19.460
[sobs]

15:19.660 --> 15:26.540
<i>♪ </i>

15:30.370 --> 15:33.250
[panting]

15:33.450 --> 15:40.250
<i>♪ </i>

15:43.600 --> 15:45.660
<i>Rowan!</i>

15:45.860 --> 15:49.010
<i>[ethereal music]</i>

15:49.210 --> 15:50.480
<i>Rowan!</i>

15:53.870 --> 15:54.960
<i>This way.</i>

15:58.230 --> 16:00.060
Rowan, this way.

16:00.260 --> 16:02.590
Mom! I'm coming!

16:02.790 --> 16:04.200
[grunts]

16:04.400 --> 16:07.290
<i>[eerie music]</i>

16:07.490 --> 16:08.550
[gasps]

16:08.750 --> 16:10.860
Rowan, over here.

16:11.050 --> 16:12.980
Mom! No! Wait!

16:15.460 --> 16:18.210
No! Mom! Don't leave!

16:18.410 --> 16:20.300
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

16:20.500 --> 16:22.300
Where are you going?

16:22.500 --> 16:23.350
Rowan.

16:23.550 --> 16:26.780
<i>♪ </i>

16:26.980 --> 16:27.820
Mom.

16:28.860 --> 16:31.790
[birds calling]

16:31.990 --> 16:33.920
I don't know, Samir.

16:34.120 --> 16:35.610
I'm really struggling
with this one.

16:37.130 --> 16:38.490
She needs to know who she is.

16:38.690 --> 16:40.100
<i>- Until we know more</i>
<i>about her,</i>

16:40.300 --> 16:41.580
<i>our job is to observe.</i>

16:41.780 --> 16:46.150
- I have observed, and...
she's scared as hell.

16:46.350 --> 16:47.670
She's lost in the woods.

16:47.870 --> 16:49.500
<i>Sip, she killed someone.</i>

16:49.700 --> 16:50.940
- Before the Talamasca
found me,

16:51.140 --> 16:53.120
I was ready
to kill someone too.

16:53.310 --> 16:55.770
It was like everything
I touched was screaming at me.

16:55.970 --> 16:57.160
My own mother
said I was the devil.

16:57.360 --> 16:58.730
<i>- And her mother</i>
<i>spent 30 years</i>

16:58.930 --> 17:00.770
<i>trying to keep her</i>
<i>out of New Orleans.</i>

17:00.970 --> 17:01.910
You tell her who she is now,

17:02.110 --> 17:03.390
she'll be
on the first plane here.

17:03.590 --> 17:04.380
Is that what you want?

17:06.730 --> 17:08.910
- Would it be worse?
<i>- We don't know.</i>

17:09.110 --> 17:10.920
<i>What we do know</i>
<i>is that many women</i>

17:11.110 --> 17:12.570
<i>in that family</i>
<i>have been haunted,</i>

17:12.770 --> 17:14.350
<i>their lives cut short,</i>
<i>and we couldn't--</i>

17:14.550 --> 17:16.660
- Again, that seems like
something she should know,

17:16.860 --> 17:18.660
if only to protect herself.

17:18.860 --> 17:20.620
- She shouldn't
have to protect herself.

17:20.820 --> 17:22.540
That's why you're there.
Right?

17:22.740 --> 17:25.060
[sighs]

17:25.260 --> 17:26.050
Right.

17:29.750 --> 17:30.930
<i>[line beeping]</i>

17:38.800 --> 17:41.990
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

17:42.190 --> 17:43.370
What's happening?

17:46.810 --> 17:48.380
- I think you must be
waking up.

17:51.120 --> 17:54.260
Do you remember the hospital?
Electroshock?

17:54.460 --> 17:56.820
You didn't even know your name,
but you found me.

17:57.950 --> 18:00.780
- I used those words,
the ones my mother taught me.

18:01.910 --> 18:03.530
Try to remember them.

18:03.730 --> 18:05.870
Quick, before I'm gone.

18:07.570 --> 18:09.050
[gasps]

18:13.840 --> 18:15.060
Wonderful.

18:16.840 --> 18:17.970
Here you are.

18:20.850 --> 18:23.980
[breathing heavily]

18:27.420 --> 18:28.780
Whoa, whoa.

18:28.980 --> 18:29.940
Sit. Sit.

18:35.690 --> 18:37.220
Don't worry, I have a lawyer

18:37.420 --> 18:39.480
who specializes
in familial situations.

18:39.680 --> 18:41.790
He's supposed to be very good.

18:41.990 --> 18:43.530
Can he get me out of here?

18:43.730 --> 18:44.790
It might take some time.

18:44.990 --> 18:46.530
Maybe a few weeks,
perhaps a month.

18:46.730 --> 18:49.230
I need to think of an excuse
for him to come see you.

18:49.430 --> 18:53.490
- Thank you for your kindness,
Doctor, but...no.

18:55.490 --> 18:56.800
I can't wait that long.

18:57.000 --> 18:59.110
<i>Ticktock, yes?</i>

18:59.310 --> 19:02.030
It's time she retire
for the evening.

19:02.230 --> 19:04.020
- Just administering
the shot now.

19:09.810 --> 19:12.860
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

19:13.060 --> 19:15.000
[whispering]
You need to be patient.

19:15.200 --> 19:20.220
<i>♪ </i>

19:20.420 --> 19:23.180
<i>[rock music playing on radio]</i>

19:23.380 --> 19:26.310
<i>♪ </i>

19:26.510 --> 19:29.050
[engine revving]

19:29.250 --> 19:33.970
<i>♪ </i>

19:34.170 --> 19:36.890
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

19:37.090 --> 19:43.970
<i>♪ </i>

19:53.630 --> 19:56.520
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

19:56.720 --> 20:03.510
<i>♪ </i>

20:05.690 --> 20:08.080
[engine revving]

20:09.690 --> 20:16.570
<i>♪ </i>

20:19.050 --> 20:19.920
Hey!

20:22.180 --> 20:23.530
Why are you following me?

20:29.970 --> 20:30.930
I'm not a threat.

20:32.850 --> 20:34.640
Who are you?

20:34.840 --> 20:36.420
<i>Are you the guy with the SUV?</i>

20:37.680 --> 20:39.730
My name is Ciprien Grieve.

20:39.930 --> 20:41.430
Is Keck paying you?

20:41.630 --> 20:43.520
No. Who's Keck?

20:43.720 --> 20:46.700
Look, let's go somewhere
where we can talk in private.

20:46.900 --> 20:48.390
I will explain everything.

20:48.590 --> 20:50.090
- Just stay--don't.

20:50.290 --> 20:51.960
- Please.
I'm not gonna hurt you.

20:52.160 --> 20:54.440
- You don't know
what I'm capable of.

20:54.640 --> 20:56.620
- I know more about you
than you think.

20:56.820 --> 20:58.580
- No.
- Please wait!

20:58.780 --> 21:00.280
[gasping]

21:00.470 --> 21:03.190
<i>[voices whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

21:03.390 --> 21:06.060
[heartbeat thumping]

21:06.260 --> 21:07.530
Come on. Come on.

21:08.710 --> 21:10.330
Come on.

21:10.530 --> 21:15.150
<i>♪ </i>

21:17.760 --> 21:19.630
- Thanks for helping, Doc.
You might have saved him.

21:21.420 --> 21:24.470
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

21:24.670 --> 21:26.260
- Uh--

21:26.460 --> 21:28.480
<i>And up.</i>

21:28.680 --> 21:31.310
<i>Okay.</i>

21:31.510 --> 21:38.440
<i>♪ </i>

21:38.640 --> 21:41.230
Sorry, you gotta follow behind.
Hospital policy.

21:41.430 --> 21:42.660
- Okay.
<i>- Yeah.</i>

21:44.440 --> 21:45.490
<i>[camera shutter snaps]</i>

21:46.960 --> 21:48.140
I'll meet you there.

21:50.230 --> 21:53.680
[engine turning over]

21:53.880 --> 21:57.810
<i>[voice whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

21:58.010 --> 22:03.730
<i>♪ </i>

22:03.930 --> 22:06.690
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

22:06.890 --> 22:12.160
<i>♪ </i>

22:22.220 --> 22:25.010
[siren wailing]

22:25.210 --> 22:32.060
<i>♪ </i>

22:32.260 --> 22:33.930
[inhales deeply]

22:34.130 --> 22:36.890
[breathing shakily]

22:37.090 --> 22:39.940
<i>[tense music]</i>

22:40.140 --> 22:41.150
Sir, wait.

22:46.550 --> 22:47.370
Hey!

22:50.990 --> 22:52.210
Where's the patient?

22:52.410 --> 22:54.170
- The guy from the beach?
- Yeah.

22:54.370 --> 22:55.560
- We tried to admit him, but he
just ripped out his IV and ran.

22:55.760 --> 22:57.170
What?

22:57.370 --> 22:58.250
- Seemed like he was in a hurry
to get somewhere.

23:09.090 --> 23:11.880
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

23:12.080 --> 23:18.930
<i>♪ </i>

23:37.120 --> 23:39.960
<i>[pensive music]</i>

23:40.160 --> 23:47.040
<i>♪ </i>

24:02.360 --> 24:05.160
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

24:05.350 --> 24:12.240
<i>♪ </i>

24:16.940 --> 24:19.470
[glass shatters]

24:19.670 --> 24:25.180
<i>♪ </i>

24:25.370 --> 24:28.180
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

24:28.380 --> 24:35.260
<i>♪ </i>

24:42.140 --> 24:43.850
<i>[P.A. system chimes]</i>

24:44.050 --> 24:45.630
<i>- Ladies and gentlemen,</i>
<i>this is your captain speaking.</i>

24:45.830 --> 24:48.370
<i>We're presently flying</i>
<i>at 35,000 feet on our flight</i>

24:48.570 --> 24:50.980
<i>from San Francisco</i>
<i>to New Orleans.</i>

24:51.180 --> 24:52.510
<i>We're expecting</i>
<i>a smooth flight</i>

24:52.710 --> 24:54.070
<i>and anticipate</i>
<i>an on-time arrival</i>

24:54.270 --> 24:56.380
<i>at Louis Armstrong</i>
<i>International Airport.</i>

24:56.580 --> 24:57.940
<i>We hope you enjoy the flight.</i>

25:03.810 --> 25:05.770
<i>[P.A. system chimes]</i>

25:07.380 --> 25:10.180
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

25:10.380 --> 25:17.220
<i>♪ </i>

26:01.610 --> 26:03.840
<i>[voices whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

26:04.040 --> 26:06.410
My love.

26:06.610 --> 26:07.710
- I haven't even
left this room,

26:07.910 --> 26:09.670
and I'm already tired.

26:09.870 --> 26:11.590
I will give you strength.

26:11.790 --> 26:15.590
Now rest.
We'll leave in the morning.

26:15.790 --> 26:17.550
What if it's too late?

26:17.750 --> 26:19.200
It won't be.

26:19.400 --> 26:21.680
She's coming to us.

26:21.880 --> 26:23.950
I've been in her dreams...

26:24.150 --> 26:25.990
leading her here.

26:26.190 --> 26:29.340
<i>["Lonely Road"]</i>

26:29.540 --> 26:32.080
You're more beautiful now
than you've ever been.

26:32.280 --> 26:36.520
<i>[haunting music]</i>

26:36.720 --> 26:39.790
<i>- ♪ They forget</i>
<i>about their lives ♪</i>

26:39.990 --> 26:42.660
<i>♪ </i>

26:42.860 --> 26:45.920
<i>♪ They forget</i>
<i>about their kids ♪</i>

26:46.120 --> 26:50.450
<i>♪ </i>

26:50.650 --> 26:52.800
<i>♪ They feel like no life </i>

26:53.000 --> 26:56.590
[both breathing heavily]

26:56.790 --> 26:59.290
[moaning]

26:59.490 --> 27:06.330
<i>♪ </i>

27:14.550 --> 27:18.300
<i>- ♪ It's like a lonely road,</i>
<i>a lonely road ♪</i>

27:18.500 --> 27:20.260
<i>♪ </i>

27:20.460 --> 27:25.830
<i>♪ It's like a lonely road,</i>
<i>a lonely road ♪</i>

27:26.030 --> 27:28.490
<i>♪ Ooh, it's like</i>
<i>a lonely road ♪</i>

27:28.690 --> 27:30.060
<i>♪ A lonely road </i>

27:30.260 --> 27:32.930
<i>♪ Lonely road </i>

27:33.130 --> 27:36.150
<i>♪ It's like a lonely road,</i>
<i>a lonely road ♪</i>

27:36.350 --> 27:37.590
[moans]

27:37.780 --> 27:40.150
<i>- ♪ Won't gain no waste</i>
<i>of time ♪</i>

27:40.350 --> 27:42.150
[moans]

27:42.350 --> 27:45.200
[panting]

27:45.400 --> 27:52.290
<i>♪ </i>

28:01.080 --> 28:04.000
- You recall when we had
that family of raccoons

28:04.200 --> 28:06.480
living in the walls,
all those...

28:06.680 --> 28:09.700
noisy little babies
Mr. Statler had to put down?

28:10.870 --> 28:12.230
It sounded just like
the sounds I heard

28:12.430 --> 28:14.310
coming from your room
last night.

28:16.050 --> 28:17.190
Mm-hmm.

28:17.390 --> 28:19.630
- Delphine,
where is my raincoat?

28:19.830 --> 28:21.240
Uh, should be by the door.

28:21.440 --> 28:23.460
- Well, I know
where it should be.

28:23.660 --> 28:25.890
[sighs] It's coming up a storm.

28:26.090 --> 28:28.290
Same day as our guild meeting.

28:28.490 --> 28:30.410
<i>The Lord has a plan,</i>
<i>but I sure don't know it.</i>

28:31.500 --> 28:32.720
Here you go.

28:34.590 --> 28:37.080
I do not trust that Dr. Lamb.

28:37.280 --> 28:39.470
<i>His people are from Boston.</i>

28:39.670 --> 28:41.340
<i>When he comes this afternoon,</i>

28:41.540 --> 28:43.430
<i>I want you</i>
<i>to keep your eyes on him.</i>

28:43.630 --> 28:46.480
- Yes, ma'am.
- And fetch Deirdre a sweater.

28:46.680 --> 28:48.430
- Poor thing'll catch a chill.
- Okay.

28:50.170 --> 28:53.140
[door clicks open and shut]

28:53.340 --> 28:56.050
<i>[dark music]</i>

28:56.250 --> 29:03.100
<i>♪ </i>

29:33.820 --> 29:35.530
<i>Miss Deirdre?</i>

29:35.730 --> 29:38.440
<i>[soft ethereal music]</i>

29:38.640 --> 29:39.620
<i>♪ </i>

29:39.820 --> 29:41.100
Please.

29:41.300 --> 29:48.140
<i>♪ </i>

30:35.620 --> 30:38.330
<i>[upbeat percussive music]</i>

30:38.530 --> 30:44.860
<i>♪ </i>

30:45.060 --> 30:46.340
[trolley bell clangs]

30:46.540 --> 30:53.380
<i>♪ </i>

30:54.950 --> 30:57.870
[indistinct chatter]

30:58.070 --> 31:00.880
<i>♪ </i>

31:01.070 --> 31:03.490
- And you remember
Margaret Kirby.

31:03.690 --> 31:04.710
- Absolutely.
- Yes.

31:04.900 --> 31:06.180
- Yes.
- So she worked very hard.

31:06.380 --> 31:10.060
<i>♪ </i>

31:10.260 --> 31:11.570
[sighs]

31:19.150 --> 31:20.420
Hi.

31:20.620 --> 31:23.330
Um, Rowan Fielding checking in.

31:23.530 --> 31:24.640
Yes.

31:24.840 --> 31:28.380
Looks like we have you
in room 1003.

31:28.580 --> 31:29.420
Great.

31:31.030 --> 31:33.120
- First time in New Orleans,
Miss Fielding?

31:33.320 --> 31:34.510
Dr. Fielding.

31:35.730 --> 31:37.520
And yes.

31:37.720 --> 31:41.000
- Spirits gravitate to historic
buildings like this one,

31:41.200 --> 31:45.010
and hotels in particular
are vectors for the dead.

31:45.210 --> 31:46.880
Here are your room keys.

31:47.080 --> 31:49.090
- Two of them, just in case.
- Thank you.

31:50.090 --> 31:52.970
Hey, um,

31:53.170 --> 31:55.930
I know this is a little weird
and a long shot,

31:56.130 --> 31:59.410
but, um, do you recognize
this house?

31:59.610 --> 32:01.810
Uh, that house...

32:02.000 --> 32:02.940
rings no bells.

32:03.140 --> 32:05.200
Okay.

32:05.400 --> 32:06.640
Thank you.

32:06.840 --> 32:08.590
- Enjoy your stay...
- Thanks.

32:08.790 --> 32:09.800
Doctor.

32:11.200 --> 32:12.020
Thank you.

32:17.420 --> 32:21.090
<i>[mellow jazz music playing]</i>

32:21.290 --> 32:23.260
[indistinct chatter]

32:23.460 --> 32:24.650
<i>[laughter]</i>

32:24.850 --> 32:29.660
<i>♪ </i>

32:29.860 --> 32:31.700
Deirdre?

32:31.900 --> 32:33.830
It can't be!

32:34.870 --> 32:36.310
It's really you!

32:37.480 --> 32:38.840
Uncle Cortland.

32:39.040 --> 32:40.100
- When they told me
you were at the door,

32:40.300 --> 32:43.060
I thought,
"Why, am I dreamin'?"

32:43.260 --> 32:46.980
My God, look at you!

32:47.180 --> 32:49.110
After all these years.

32:49.310 --> 32:51.510
We both got old, didn't we?

32:51.710 --> 32:53.810
It's not right,

32:54.010 --> 32:56.820
the way she kept you like that.

32:57.020 --> 33:00.260
Oh, I should have
never let you go.

33:00.450 --> 33:02.130
I need your help.

33:02.330 --> 33:04.650
- Well, whatever I can do,
I will.

33:04.850 --> 33:06.830
But, uh--

33:07.030 --> 33:09.440
uh...

33:09.640 --> 33:12.010
where is he?

33:12.210 --> 33:14.300
- After all this time,
I still never know.

33:15.610 --> 33:17.000
Ah.

33:18.920 --> 33:21.450
Well, what matters
is that you're here.

33:21.650 --> 33:23.540
You're here!

33:23.740 --> 33:25.980
So let's get you
cleaned up, hmm?

33:26.180 --> 33:27.280
Come on.

33:27.480 --> 33:30.020
<i>♪ When you see me </i>

33:30.220 --> 33:33.590
<i>♪ Walking around </i>

33:33.790 --> 33:36.510
<i>♪ When you see him </i>

33:36.710 --> 33:39.640
<i>♪ Walking around </i>

33:39.840 --> 33:42.650
<i>♪ When you see me </i>

33:42.840 --> 33:46.650
<i>♪ Creeping around </i>

33:46.850 --> 33:50.350
- Hey. Hi.
You're a tour guide, right?

33:50.550 --> 33:52.440
- Next one's at 5:00.
We meet at the front desk.

33:52.640 --> 33:54.050
No. Well, maybe.

33:54.250 --> 33:57.750
But I was just wondering,
do you know this place?

33:57.950 --> 33:59.840
Oh, um, that's--

34:00.040 --> 34:03.230
I--I got hers, and I'll have
one for me, please.

34:03.430 --> 34:05.320
Yes.

34:05.520 --> 34:07.370
- Yeah?
- It's the old Mayfair house.

34:07.570 --> 34:09.280
- The May--Mayfair?

34:09.480 --> 34:10.760
It's not on the tour anymore.

34:10.960 --> 34:13.370
Family paid
to have it taken off.

34:13.570 --> 34:14.590
Okay.

34:14.790 --> 34:16.420
What do you know
about--about it?

34:16.620 --> 34:18.030
- Thank you.
- Oh, all kinds of things.

34:18.230 --> 34:19.380
Parties at the turn
of the century

34:19.580 --> 34:21.030
that went on for days,

34:21.230 --> 34:24.510
murders, disappearances,
ghosts.

34:24.710 --> 34:26.780
- Ghosts.
- Oh, heck yeah.

34:26.980 --> 34:29.260
There's ghosts everywhere
in New Orleans.

34:29.460 --> 34:33.080
But really, that house
is famous for its witches.

34:35.560 --> 34:37.470
Sorry, what?

34:38.470 --> 34:41.660
- Witches, vampires, demons.
[laughs]

34:41.860 --> 34:45.490
Oh, honey, we make up all kinds
of hooey on these tours.

34:45.690 --> 34:47.530
Folks slop it up
with a biscuit.

34:53.790 --> 34:56.810
- Do you think maybe you could,
uh, take a little detour

34:57.010 --> 34:59.290
and point that house out to me?

34:59.490 --> 35:02.160
- Tour leaves at 5:00.
- Great.

35:02.360 --> 35:05.860
- Bye.
<i>- ♪ See me creeping around </i>

35:06.060 --> 35:09.200
<i>♪ When you see him </i>

35:14.030 --> 35:16.960
Oh, there she is.

35:17.160 --> 35:20.000
- Oh, such a pretty thing.
- [chuckles]

35:20.200 --> 35:22.400
- You know, that is
my daughter's old dress.

35:22.600 --> 35:24.230
- When I was a child,
you used to buy me

35:24.420 --> 35:27.180
dresses just like this
every year for my birthday.

35:27.380 --> 35:28.230
Do you remember?

35:28.430 --> 35:29.800
Of course. Of course.

35:30.000 --> 35:31.670
[chuckles]
Someone had to.

35:31.870 --> 35:34.710
Carlotta had you
in those hideous old sacks.

35:34.910 --> 35:36.630
<i>- And every year, no matter</i>
<i>where I hid them,</i>

35:36.830 --> 35:39.020
she would find those dresses

35:39.220 --> 35:41.940
and slice them up
with kitchen shears.

35:42.140 --> 35:44.450
It's almost worse
than never having them at all.

35:46.930 --> 35:48.420
Hmm.

35:48.620 --> 35:51.990
You know, I can't imagine
all you have been through.

35:52.190 --> 35:54.390
- Hmm.
- My daughter's alive.

35:54.590 --> 35:56.780
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

35:56.980 --> 35:58.160
Alive?

36:00.170 --> 36:01.910
Are you sure, now?

36:02.110 --> 36:03.520
Lasher's seen her.

36:06.300 --> 36:07.530
How could this happen?

36:07.730 --> 36:09.710
Carlotta stole her from me,

36:09.900 --> 36:11.050
hid her away.

36:13.130 --> 36:16.280
But she's grown up,
and she's coming here.

36:16.480 --> 36:17.930
- Oh, well, the two of you
will have to stay here.

36:18.130 --> 36:19.450
I'll have rooms prepared.

36:19.650 --> 36:20.710
Thank you.

36:21.930 --> 36:22.880
- Wh--where is she?

36:24.280 --> 36:26.200
He's going to show me.

36:26.400 --> 36:33.200
<i>♪ </i>

36:39.420 --> 36:42.650
[breathes deeply]

36:42.850 --> 36:45.870
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

36:46.070 --> 36:49.310
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

36:49.510 --> 36:52.180
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

36:52.380 --> 36:53.310
[items rattling]

36:53.510 --> 36:56.140
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

36:56.340 --> 36:59.230
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

36:59.430 --> 37:01.370
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera.</i>

37:01.570 --> 37:04.410
[shower running]

37:04.610 --> 37:11.410
<i>♪ </i>

37:28.950 --> 37:32.000
<i>Mi Daemon, ad me veni.</i>

37:32.200 --> 37:35.180
<i>Mi Daemon, mihi labora.</i>

37:35.380 --> 37:37.180
<i>Mi Daemon, me libera!</i>

37:37.380 --> 37:39.880
Yes. Yes!

37:40.080 --> 37:42.150
[electricity crackling]

37:42.340 --> 37:49.230
<i>♪ </i>

37:59.890 --> 38:02.770
[items rattling]

38:02.970 --> 38:09.770
<i>♪ </i>

38:40.930 --> 38:42.210
No!

38:42.400 --> 38:49.290
<i>♪ </i>

39:31.720 --> 39:34.130
[gasps]

39:34.330 --> 39:35.390
She's already here.

39:35.590 --> 39:37.380
[gasps]

39:39.730 --> 39:41.390
I'll have my driver take you.

39:50.610 --> 39:53.400
[phone buzzing]

39:59.970 --> 40:02.940
- Hello?
- I need to see you right away.

40:03.140 --> 40:04.460
<i>You're alive.</i>

40:04.660 --> 40:08.940
- A little shaken up,
but yeah, I'm alive.

40:09.140 --> 40:10.860
Who are you?

40:11.060 --> 40:13.690
Why do you have
pictures of me on your phone?

40:13.890 --> 40:15.730
My name is Ciprien Grieve.

40:15.930 --> 40:18.950
I work for an organization
called the Talamasca.

40:19.150 --> 40:22.170
Your mother, Ellie,
she reached out to us.

40:22.370 --> 40:24.390
<i>She wanted me to protect you.</i>

40:24.590 --> 40:27.220
- So she knew who I was
but she didn't want me to know?

40:27.420 --> 40:29.880
What--that--why--
why would she do that?

40:30.080 --> 40:31.620
<i>- She thought</i>
<i>she was helping you.</i>

40:31.820 --> 40:33.400
Please, I--I will
explain everything

40:33.600 --> 40:34.880
once you're somewhere safe.

40:35.080 --> 40:36.710
Why should I believe you?

40:36.910 --> 40:38.760
<i>- 'Cause I know</i>
<i>what you're capable of,</i>

40:38.960 --> 40:40.620
and I can help you control it.

40:43.140 --> 40:45.330
- I--I don't understand

40:45.530 --> 40:47.460
anything that's happening
to me.

40:47.660 --> 40:50.070
I haven't for a long time now.

40:50.270 --> 40:51.640
<i>I know the feeling.</i>

40:51.840 --> 40:54.420
The man who taught me
about my gift

40:54.620 --> 40:55.950
told me this story about a man

40:56.150 --> 40:57.910
who had been wandering lost
in the woods.

40:58.110 --> 41:00.690
<i>And one day, he saw</i>
<i>another man who was also lost.</i>

41:00.890 --> 41:02.820
<i>He said, "Let's go together."</i>

41:03.020 --> 41:05.260
Second man said,
"Why should I go with you?"

41:05.460 --> 41:07.260
First man answered,

41:07.460 --> 41:10.050
"Because I can show you
which ways didn't work for me,

41:10.250 --> 41:12.490
"and you can show me
which ways didn't work for you.

41:12.690 --> 41:14.840
<i>Together, we'll find our way."</i>

41:15.040 --> 41:18.800
<i>[inquisitive music]</i>

41:19.000 --> 41:22.280
- I'll be in the lobby of the
Pontchartrain in five minutes.

41:22.480 --> 41:23.800
But you probably
already knew that.

41:24.000 --> 41:25.720
[chuckles]

41:25.920 --> 41:26.800
I'll be there.

41:27.000 --> 41:31.940
<i>♪ </i>

41:32.140 --> 41:34.860
[sniffles]

41:35.060 --> 41:37.120
- Not being critical,
but Margaret Kirby

41:37.320 --> 41:38.850
was able--
[wind gusts]

41:47.690 --> 41:48.830
Deirdre?

41:49.030 --> 41:55.360
<i>♪ </i>

41:55.550 --> 41:56.610
Deirdre.

41:58.130 --> 41:59.880
Deirdre, I don't know
what is happening,

42:00.080 --> 42:03.230
but I am taking you home.

42:03.430 --> 42:04.970
I'm not coming home with you.

42:05.170 --> 42:06.890
Oh, yes, you are.

42:07.090 --> 42:09.240
Who did this to you?
Was it that Dr. Lamb?

42:09.440 --> 42:11.330
Let go of me.

42:11.530 --> 42:13.240
You are not keeping me
from my daughter.

42:13.440 --> 42:15.290
Oh, sweetheart.

42:15.490 --> 42:18.160
[breathing sharply]

42:18.360 --> 42:19.240
Sweetheart.

42:21.810 --> 42:24.470
Your daughter is long dead,

42:24.670 --> 42:28.420
and you are a sick,
sick, sick little bird.

42:30.820 --> 42:32.480
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

42:32.680 --> 42:35.260
- You understand
that if I'm awake now,

42:35.460 --> 42:36.740
so is he.

42:36.940 --> 42:43.740
<i>♪ </i>

42:59.450 --> 43:02.110
<i>[voices whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

43:06.290 --> 43:08.080
[keys rattling]

43:08.280 --> 43:12.210
<i>♪ </i>

43:12.410 --> 43:13.610
[elevator bell dings]

43:13.810 --> 43:20.610
<i>♪ </i>

43:34.660 --> 43:37.500
<i>["Eternally"]</i>

43:37.700 --> 43:40.550
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

43:40.750 --> 43:43.810
<i>[soft ethereal music]</i>

43:44.010 --> 43:50.420
<i>♪ </i>

43:53.250 --> 43:55.340
[breathes deeply]

43:55.540 --> 43:58.830
<i>♪ </i>

43:59.030 --> 44:00.650
[elevator bell dings]

44:00.850 --> 44:07.660
<i>♪ </i>

44:07.860 --> 44:09.520
[sighs]

44:11.130 --> 44:12.880
[elevator bell dings]

44:13.080 --> 44:19.190
<i>♪ </i>

44:27.150 --> 44:28.020
It's you.

44:29.630 --> 44:32.950
<i>♪ Duck </i>

44:33.150 --> 44:35.780
[body thuds]

44:35.980 --> 44:37.650
[gasping]

44:37.850 --> 44:41.700
[screaming]

44:41.890 --> 44:46.130
<i>♪ I long to be </i>

44:46.330 --> 44:51.920
<i>♪ Eternally yours </i>

44:52.120 --> 44:55.320
<i>♪ </i>

44:55.520 --> 45:00.190
<i>♪ Just like my mother </i>

45:00.390 --> 45:01.930
<i>♪ </i>

45:02.130 --> 45:07.460
<i>♪ Just like my father </i>

45:07.660 --> 45:12.200
<i>♪ It's what feels good to me </i>

45:12.400 --> 45:17.250
<i>♪ What feels good to me </i>

45:17.450 --> 45:19.330
<i>♪ </i>

45:21.420 --> 45:24.600
<i>♪ Ooh </i>

45:26.470 --> 45:29.260
♪

45:29.460 --> 45:31.050
Come with me.
We'll go to the house.

45:31.250 --> 45:32.090
You'll be safer there.

45:32.290 --> 45:33.090
[ Gasps ]

45:33.290 --> 45:34.570
What are you
gonna do?

45:34.770 --> 45:37.010
Sip:
There is a being.

45:37.210 --> 45:38.710
He might start to visit you.

45:38.910 --> 45:40.190
They call him Lasher.

45:40.390 --> 45:41.760
He's close to me
somehow.

45:41.950 --> 45:43.150
I'm sure
you'll find a way in.

45:43.350 --> 45:45.590
♪

45:45.780 --> 45:47.720
It's a
murder investigation.

45:47.920 --> 45:49.460
God forgive you.

45:49.660 --> 45:51.330
She's a witch.

45:51.530 --> 45:55.410
♪

45:56.460 --> 46:00.640
♪

46:00.840 --> 46:02.210
Lasher: You remember,
I promised you once

46:02.410 --> 46:04.260
that your life would change.

46:04.460 --> 46:06.120
That everything would be better.

46:07.550 --> 46:10.910
I remember.
[Whispers] Yeah.

46:11.110 --> 46:12.480
That change is coming,
my love.

46:12.680 --> 46:14.480
So, this episode is called
"The Dark Place,"

46:14.680 --> 46:16.570
and that was really
the phrase that we used

46:16.770 --> 46:19.530
in the writer's room when we
were talking about the space

46:19.730 --> 46:23.540
in Dierdre's mind that she lives
and inhabits with Lasher.

46:23.740 --> 46:25.020
Lasher: I found your daughter.

46:25.220 --> 46:26.500
She's alive.

46:26.690 --> 46:30.540
For 30 years, Dierdre
has been in a stupor,

46:30.740 --> 46:34.200
and, so, her only
real activity has been

46:34.400 --> 46:38.380
to be inside her own mind
in conversation with Lasher.

46:38.580 --> 46:40.730
I need to see her.

46:40.930 --> 46:43.290
Then you need to wake up
and take control.

46:43.490 --> 46:45.470
Use the power
that's readily yours.

46:45.670 --> 46:47.210
♪

46:47.410 --> 46:50.740
Both Dierdre and Rowan
are in this dark place,

46:50.940 --> 46:53.960
and the journey of the episode
is to watch them move

46:54.160 --> 46:56.090
closer and closer to each other.

46:56.290 --> 46:57.660
Are you okay?

46:57.860 --> 47:09.930
♪

47:10.130 --> 47:12.670
[Gasping, groaning]

47:12.870 --> 47:15.810
Esta: Rowan is in this very,
very dark place.

47:16.010 --> 47:17.810
She has done
this monstrous thing.

47:18.010 --> 47:19.550
She has killed this man,

47:19.750 --> 47:21.990
and she's trying to understand
that, and to cope with that.

47:22.190 --> 47:25.210
♪

47:25.410 --> 47:27.160
But she's such a guarded person

47:27.360 --> 47:30.170
that she's never gonna let on
that she isn't fine.

47:30.370 --> 47:32.170
Woman: You've been through
a great deal of trauma,

47:32.370 --> 47:34.690
and there's nothing wrong
with acknowledging that.

47:34.890 --> 47:36.040
I have acknowledged it.

47:36.240 --> 47:39.260
We see that she's
absolutely falling apart.

47:39.460 --> 47:40.660
Fuck.

47:40.860 --> 47:41.880
[Crows cawing]

47:42.070 --> 47:43.920
[Whispers calling] <i>Rowan.</i>

47:44.120 --> 47:45.140
♪

47:45.340 --> 47:47.180
[Cawing intensifies]

47:47.380 --> 47:49.580
♪

47:49.780 --> 47:51.670
Esta: And, of course,
Ciprien sees this.

47:51.870 --> 47:53.840
He is pushing at the Talamasca

47:54.040 --> 47:57.150
to be allowed to tell Rowan
her story.

47:57.350 --> 47:59.370
It seems like something
she should know.

47:59.570 --> 48:00.940
If only to protect herself.

48:01.140 --> 48:02.720
<i>She shouldn't have to</i>
<i>protect herself.</i>

48:02.920 --> 48:04.720
That's why you're there, right?

48:04.920 --> 48:09.730
♪

48:09.930 --> 48:12.780
Esta: Rowan is convinced that
she's being followed

48:12.970 --> 48:15.000
because of what happened
with Lemle.

48:15.190 --> 48:19.300
Her suspicion is that somebody
has a private eye following her

48:19.500 --> 48:21.650
trying to see what she's doing,
what she's done.

48:21.850 --> 48:23.310
Hey!

48:23.510 --> 48:24.660
Why are you following me?

48:24.860 --> 48:26.400
And when
Ciprien steps out,

48:26.600 --> 48:28.310
she knows that
she could hurt him.

48:28.510 --> 48:30.920
She knows that
she's not in any danger.

48:31.120 --> 48:33.270
I'm not a threat.
Who are you?

48:33.470 --> 48:35.490
She's not sure how to
control what happens,

48:35.690 --> 48:37.760
but I don't thing she's
afraid for herself.

48:37.960 --> 48:40.540
She's scared of what
she could do to other people.

48:40.740 --> 48:42.240
I will explain everything.

48:42.440 --> 48:43.760
Just stay --
Don't --

48:43.960 --> 48:45.770
Please,
I'm not gonna hurt you.

48:45.960 --> 48:47.770
You don't know
what I'm capable of.

48:47.970 --> 48:50.470
I know more about you
than you think.Just --

48:50.660 --> 48:51.600
Pease, wait!

48:51.800 --> 48:52.900
♪

48:53.100 --> 48:54.120
[Gasps deeply]

48:54.320 --> 48:59.690
♪

48:59.890 --> 49:01.260
[Cellphone unlocks]

49:01.460 --> 49:02.520
♪

49:02.720 --> 49:03.830
I'll meet you there.

49:04.030 --> 49:05.050
[Door slams shut]

49:05.240 --> 49:06.310
Esta: Who was this person?

49:06.510 --> 49:08.270
Why are these images
on the phone?

49:08.470 --> 49:12.230
She's more confused than ever,
but she also has her first clue.

49:12.430 --> 49:14.320
Ciprien's gone ahead in the
ambulance, so it's like,

49:14.510 --> 49:16.230
I've gotta get back
to him and ask him.

49:16.430 --> 49:18.060
She has to have an answer.

49:18.260 --> 49:19.670
And, of course,
when she gets to the hospital,

49:19.870 --> 49:20.890
he's not there.

49:21.090 --> 49:25.240
♪

49:25.440 --> 49:28.200
You know, I can't imagine
all you have been through.

49:28.400 --> 49:29.720
[Bottles clank]

49:29.920 --> 49:31.330
My daughter's alive.

49:31.530 --> 49:32.680
[Slurps]

49:32.880 --> 49:35.080
Lasher's seen her.

49:35.270 --> 49:37.950
Cortland is very surprised
that Rowan is alive.

49:38.150 --> 49:39.430
How could this happen?

49:39.630 --> 49:41.260
Carlotta stole her from me.

49:41.450 --> 49:42.730
Hid her away.

49:42.930 --> 49:45.780
It really is a mystery
to everyone in the family

49:45.980 --> 49:47.610
that Dierdre's daughter
has survived.

49:47.810 --> 49:48.960
Where is she?

49:49.160 --> 49:50.740
He's going to show me.

49:50.940 --> 49:54.960
I really wanted to have
a moment where we se Dierdre

49:55.160 --> 49:59.230
as a full, powerful
woman and witch.

49:59.430 --> 50:01.670
[Speaking Latin]

50:01.870 --> 50:04.410
♪

50:04.610 --> 50:07.760
Where we get to see what Dierdre
would have been her whole life

50:07.960 --> 50:10.720
if she got to inhabit
her full witchy power.

50:10.920 --> 50:14.290
And now, for the first time,
she does.

50:14.490 --> 50:16.160
She summons Lasher.

50:16.360 --> 50:17.990
She sends him out to find Rowan,

50:18.190 --> 50:20.380
and then she sees
through his eyes

50:20.580 --> 50:22.510
and is able to find
her daughter.

50:22.710 --> 50:31.610
♪

50:31.810 --> 50:33.130
She's already here!

50:33.330 --> 50:35.180
[Breathing heavily]

50:35.380 --> 50:40.310
♪

50:40.510 --> 50:43.670
I was trying to think
how can we have them connect

50:43.860 --> 50:45.800
and then have it all vanish.

50:46.000 --> 50:48.150
And that hallway
and that elevator

50:48.350 --> 50:51.930
felt absolutely perfect
to the moment.

50:52.130 --> 50:54.020
Part of Rowan's journey
into the family

50:54.220 --> 50:56.030
is to understand
who her mother was,

50:56.230 --> 50:58.160
to understand
her mother's death.

50:58.360 --> 51:01.600
And this seemed like an
extraordinarily symbolic

51:01.800 --> 51:03.160
way to do it.

51:03.360 --> 51:04.510
Part the curtain again,

51:04.710 --> 51:06.080
have them meet each other
for a moment,

51:06.280 --> 51:08.470
and then have it all fall apart.

51:08.670 --> 51:13.170
♪

51:13.370 --> 51:14.390
It's you.

51:14.590 --> 51:16.650
♪

51:16.850 --> 51:19.140
[Body thuds]

51:19.340 --> 51:20.310
Ahh!

51:20.510 --> 51:21.880
Rowan: Ahh! Ahhhh!

51:22.080 --> 51:24.310
[Breathing frantically]

51:24.510 --> 51:30.090
♪
